  "abstract": "ICRISAT hosted a workshop on \"The Role of Small Watershed Hydrology in\r\nRainfed Agriculture\" from 22-24 November 1988 at ICRISAT Center. Some 30\r\nparticipants from research institutions in India and one from Thailand joined ICRI -\r\nSAT scientists in their deliberations.\r\nThe workshop aimed at exploring linkages for collaborative research by reviewing\r\npast experience, and as a basis for a new research agenda. As the scientists represented\r\nwide experience on watershed hydrology, the discussions achieved a general perspective\r\nthrough exchanges of information and ideas.\r\nPresented in this volume are the welcome address, the recommendations of the\r\nworkshop, and abstracts of the papers. The Indian Society of Dryland Agriculture is\r\nplanning a special issue of its journal to incorporate many of the papers presented at\r\nthe workshop.\r\nWhile man cannot control weather, he can cushion the impact of adverse weather\r\nconditions—manifested in drought and floods—on rainfed agriculture by learning to\r\nplan and manage his land and water resources more efficiently. ICRISAT hopes that\r\nthis volume and the one proposed by the Indian Society of Dryland Agriculture will\r\nhelp us move forward.",
